Pre-Game Insights: Kenya were denied an opportunity to add to their six AFCON appearances due to a FIFA ban for governmental interference.
Kenya has a positive record against Zimbabwe with three wins and a draw from four previous meetings.
Kenya is on a six-match unbeaten streak in their last seven matches.
Zimbabwe were also banned by FIFA from taking part in the last AFCON qualifying campaign.
Zimbabwe's form has been mixed with three wins and four losses in their seven outings this year.
Kenya's Michael Olunga is doubtful due to injury, while Zimbabwe's Khama Billiat is returning from retirement.
